  "response": "Yes, Bill Clinton was involved in several high-profile affairs during his marriage to Hillary Clinton, most notably the Monica Lewinsky scandal in the late 1990s. Lewinsky, a White House intern at the time, had a sexual relationship with President Clinton, which he initially denied but later admitted to during a grand jury investigation. This scandal led to Clinton's impeachment by the House of Representatives for perjury and obstruction of justice, though he was acquitted by the Senate.\n\nHillary Clinton\u2019s response to these affairs, particularly the Lewinsky scandal, was complex. She initially defended her husband publicly, characterizing the situation as part of a \"vast right-wing conspiracy\" aimed at undermining his presidency. Privately, however, she reportedly faced significant emotional turmoil and anger. Over time, she worked to separate her political and professional identity from her personal life, maintaining her focus on her own career in public service.\n\nTheir marriage has remained intact, and both have indicated that they worked through their issues privately. Hillary Clinton has since spoken about the challenges of their relationship in her memoir, *Living History* (2003), and her 2017 book, *What Happened*. She has emphasized forgiveness and resilience as key factors in their ability to move forward together.",
